\parbox{3.5in}{Because the displacement at $b$ in the real structure is 0, 
it is not quite so tricky to get the signs right. $\Delta_b = 0$ is on one side 
of the compatibility equation, and it doesn't matter if it is $+0$ or $-0$.
If support $b$ settled or was elastic, more care would be required.}

\parbox{3.5in}{This sketch does {\em not} establish a sign convention
for displacements. The direction of the unit virtual load does that.

We have sketched the displacement to be consistent with the sign
we establish below, even though we suspect displacement
will be downward. $\Delta_{b0}$ will come out
with the proper sign.
}

text.tspan: Flexibility coefficients (displacements due to unit redundants):

g.ns0:text: \\parbox{3.5in}{The sign convention for displacements is +ive {\\bf upwards}.}\n
